{{Infobox Airline | airline=Africa World Airlines| logo=AfricaWorldAirlines2016newlogo.png| logo_size=| fleet_size=7| destinations=8| IATA=AW| ICAO=AFW| callsign=BLACKSTAR| parent=[[HNA Group]]| founded=2010| commenced=21 September 2012| headquarters= [[Accra]], [[Greater Accra Region|Greater Accra]], [[Ghana]]| key_people= Quan "John" Xiaoyi<small> ([[CEO]])</small><ref>https://www.flyawa.com.gh/executive-management/</ref>, [[Togbe Afede XIV]] <small>([[Organizational founder|Founder]])</small><ref>https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/business/Togbe-Afede-s-Airline-Takes-Delivery-of-Second-Aircraft-250076</ref>| bases=[[Kotoka International Airport]]| focus_cities=| company_slogan=''"Touching Africa, Touching The World"''| frequent_flyer=| lounge=| alliance=| website= [http://www.flyAfricaWorld.com/ flyAfricaWorld.com]| |image=|aoc=|hubs=|num_employees=}}
'''Africa World Airlines Limited''' ('''AWA''') is a [[Ghana]]ian airline company with its head office in [[Accra]], [[Greater Accra Region|Greater Accra]], [[Ghana]],<ref>"[https://www.flyawa.com.gh/contact/]." Africa World Airlines. Retrieved on 6 May 2013. </ref> and its main hub at [[Kotoka International Airport]] in Accra.
==History== Africa World Airlines was incorporated in 2010 and commenced flights in 2012. It is a joint venture between [[Hainan Airlines]], [[China-Africa Development Fund]], [[SSNIT]] and SAS Finance Group<ref name="ATWOnline">{{cite web|title= Hainan Airlines, Africa World Airlines launch JV|url= http://atwonline.com/airline-finance-data/news/hainan-ghana-s-africa-world-airlines-launch-jv-0725|publisher= Air Transport World}}</ref> .<ref name="Bravia">{{cite web|title= HNA Group and Africa World Airlines sign Joint Venture Agreement|url= http://www.braviacapital.com/news/hna-group-and-africa-world-airlines-sign-joint-venture-agreement/|publisher= Bravia Capital|access-date= 2012-08-29|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20121118080913/http://www.braviacapital.com/news/hna-group-and-africa-world-airlines-sign-joint-venture-agreement/|archive-date= 2012-11-18|dead-url= yes|df= }}</ref>
==Fleet== ===Current Fleet=== [[File:9GAET in Kumasi.jpg|An Africa World Airlines ERJ-145LR at [[Kumasi Airport]].|thumb|right]]
The Africa World Airlines fleet consists of the following aircraft (as of October 2018)<ref>{{cite web|title= Africa World Airlines Fleet|url=https://www.flightradar24.com/data/airlines/aw-afw/fleet|publisher=FlightRadar24}}</ref>: <center> {| class="toccolours" border="1" cellpadding="3" style="border-collapse:collapse" |+ '''Africa World Airlines fleet''' |- bgcolor=#ccccff !rowspan="2"|Aircraft !rowspan="2"|In Service !colspan="3"|Passengers |- bgcolor=#ccccff !B !E !Total |- |[[Embraer ERJ 145 family|Embraer ERJ-145LI]] |align="center"|7 |0 |50 |50<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ch-aviation.ch/portal/airline.php?cha=AFW|title=Africa World Airlines on ch-aviation|author=|date=|website=ch-aviation}}</ref> |- |align="center"|'''Total''' |<center>'''7''' |colspan="6"| |} </center>
===Fleet development=== Africa World Airlines took delivery on 30 August 2012 of its first [[Embraer 145]] aircraft that will be used to operate domestic routes. .<ref name="GhanaianTimes">{{cite web|title= Africa World Airlines First Aircraft Lands|url= http://www.ghana.gov.gh/index.php/news/features/15755-africa-world-airlines-first-aircraft-lands|publisher= The Ghanaian Times}}</ref> A second aircraft was delivered on 8 September 2012.<ref name="JetPhotos.net">{{cite web|title= 9G-AEU Africa World Airlines|url= http://jetphotos.net/viewphoto.php?id=7445277&nseq=0|publisher= JetPhotos.net|access-date= 2012-10-06|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140911103944/http://jetphotos.net/viewphoto.php?id=7445277&nseq=0|archive-date= 2014-09-11|dead-url= yes|df= }}</ref>. The airline added a 3rd aircraft in 2013 and a further 4 aircraft between 2016 and 2018. All these aircraft were previously operated by [[Tianjin Airlines]] which is a sister company within the [[HNA Group]].<ref>{{cite web |title= Africa World Airlines Finalizing Launch Plans for ERJ-145 |url= http://www.ch-aviation.ch/portal/news/12168-africa-world-finalizing-launch-plans-for-erj-145-domestic-operation |work= CH Aviation}}</ref>
