'''Bibiani Gold Stars FC''', formerly the '''Complex Stars''' and often shortened to and more commonly known as the '''Gold Stars''', is a [[Ghanaian]] professional [[football team]]. It was founded in 1998 and later given to the Bibiani Gold Mines, who play in the 2A Zone of the [[Ghana Football Leagues|Ghana Division One League]].<ref name="piojiojoo">{{cite web | url=http://www.ghanafa.org/pages/divisiononeleague/ | title=Division One League | publisher=ghanafa.org | accessdate=19 August 2013}}</ref> Zone 2A has seven competing teams from the part of the [[Ashanti Region]], [[Western Region (Ghana)|Western Region]] and the [[Central Region (Ghana)|Central Region]] of Ghana.<ref name="piojiojoo"/>
