{{One source|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox ethnic group | group = Comorians in France | image = | caption = | population = '''100.000''' | popplace = [[Marseille]], [[Paris]], [[Seine-Saint-Denis]], [[Lyon]], [[Mayotte]] | langs = [[Comorian language|Shikomor]], [[French language|French]], [[Arabic language|Arabic]] | rels = [[Sunni Islam]] | related = [[Black people in France]], [[Afro-French]] }}
'''Comorians in France''' consist of migrants from [[Comoros]] and their descendants living and working in France.
Outside of [[Mayotte]], where Comorians are an important proportion of the local population, a great Comorian community is settled in [[Metropolitan France]], mostly in [[Marseille]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slateafrique.com/92217/marseille-capitale-comorienne |title=Marseille, la plus grande ville comorienne |publisher=Slate Afrique |date= |accessdate=2013-09-08}}</ref> but also in [[Paris]] and [[Seine-Saint-Denis]], [[Lyon]] and [[Dunkerque]].
