The '''Constitution of the Italian Republic''' ({{lang-it|Costituzione della Repubblica Italiana}}), was the [[constitution]] of the [[Italian Republic (Napoleonic)|Italian Republic]], a [[French client republic|client republic]] of [[First French Republic|France]] under [[Napoleon|Napoleon Bonaparte]], roughly comprising the modern-day [[Northern Italy|northern]] [[Regions of Italy|region]]s of [[Lombardy]] and [[Emilia-Romagna]]. It came into effect on 26 January 1802.
