'''Egypt–Uruguay relations''' are the relations between [[Egypt]] and [[Uruguay]]. <!-- Both countries established diplomatic relations in 1XXX. --> Egypt has an embassy in [[Montevideo]].<ref>[http://embassy-finder.com/egypt_in_montevideo_uruguay Embassy of Egypt in Montevideo] Retrieved 11 September 2013.</ref> Uruguay has an embassy in [[Cairo]]<ref>[http://embassy-finder.com/uruguay_in_cairo_egypt Embassy of Uruguay in Cairo] Retrieved 11 September 2013.</ref> and a consulate in Alexandria.<ref>[http://embassy-finder.com/uruguay_in_alexandria_egypt Uruguayan Consulate in Alexandria] Retrieved 11 September 2013.</ref>

Both countries are members of the [[Group of 77]].

==Trade==
In trading relationships, Egypt is an important trading partner for Uruguay, with over USD 26m in soybean sales;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lr21.com.uy/economia/1083526-record-absoluto-exportaciones-uruguayas-trepan-a-8-751-millones-de-dolares-en-2012-con-explosivos-crecimientos-a-nuevos-destinos|title=Notable growth of Uruguay's exports to new destination countries|date=11 January 2013|work=[[La República]]|accessdate=14 September 2013}} {{es icon}}</ref> Egypt is also an important buyer of Uruguayan lambs.<ref>[http://www.planagropecuario.org.uy/publicaciones/revista/R130/R_130_60.pdf Uruguay's exports of live cattle] ([[Portable Document Format|PDF]]) {{es icon}}</ref> Since 2004 there is a Framework Agreement between Egypt and the Mercosur countries.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www0.parlamento.gub.uy/htmlstat/pl/acuerdos/acue460-A.htm |title=Mercosur-Egypt Framework Agreement |date=7 July 2004 |publisher=Parliament of Uruguay |accessdate=14 September 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070914151406/http://www.parlamento.gub.uy/htmlstat/pl/acuerdos/acue460-A.htm |archivedate=14 September 2007 |df= }} {{es icon}}</ref>

==Culture==
Montevideo has a small Ancient Egyptian Museum,<ref>[http://www.museos.gub.uy/index.php?option=com_k2&view=item&id=153:museo-egipcio-de-la-sociedad-uruguaya-de-egitolog%C3%ACa&Itemid=43 Egyptian Museum in Montevideo] Retrieved 15 September 2013.</ref> held by the Uruguayan Society of Egyptology (established 1980);<ref>[http://www.egyptologyforum.org/bbs/uruguay/Uruguay.htm Uruguayan Society of Egyptology] Retrieved 15 September 2013.</ref> a notable Uruguayan Egyptologist is Juan José Castillos.<ref>[http://www.reocities.com/duarts/index2.html Publications of the Uruguayan Society of Egyptology] Retrieved 15 September 2013. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150311023743/http://www.reocities.com/duarts/index2.html |date=March 11, 2015 }}</ref>

There is an Egyptian Center for Islamic Culture in Montevideo.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.espectador.com/perspectiva/entrevistas/ent0110013.htm |title=Interview to Amed Awad Abdallah, religious principal of the Egyptian Center for Islamic Culture |publisher=[[CX 14 El Espectador]] |language=es |archivedate=4 October 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081004055617/http://www.espectador.com/perspectiva/entrevistas/ent0110013.htm |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>

